 bank myrtle beach were founded by local business leaders committed to building successful banks in both cities under the umbrella of parent holding company carolina financial corporation the reason for both banks forming was the same as a response to several large bank mergers that left few community banking choices for area residents and businessescarolina financial corporation was founded in 7 in charleston and quickly introduced community firstbank expanding over the course of  years the bank grew to six locations throughout the area providing banking products and exceptional service to the greater charleston marketin order to bring the community banking atmosphere back to myrtle beach carolina financial corporation partnered with business leaders in the myrtle beach area to form another community bank – crescent bank through the years crescent bank grew to four fullservice locations to meet the banking needs of grand strand residents and businesses after  years of operating the banks as two independent banks the board of directors and management recognized consolidating the two banks into one would create more opportunities and better service to their customersas a result on march 6  the firms sister banks consolidated to become one bank – crescom bank the name and the logo pay tribute to its former brands by using elements from both crescent and community firstbank along with the crescent moon which is such an iconic brand element of the stateconsolidated now crescom bank has  locations along the coast of south carolina offering a strong core of banking products and services and a committed group of community leaders management and personnel crescom bank remains committed to warm exceptional service and a strong knowledge of local businesses and economic trendsit’s this dedication that makes have a nice bank more than just a slogan but a commitment to service this combined with the years of experience and unique understanding of financial opportunities along coastal south carolina makes crescom bank the perfect fit for customers personal or business financial needsthe company believes that community involvement is a vital key to understanding the needs of both the grand strand and the charleston markets they strive to know customers by customers name and not just a number and as always we strive to understand and assist customers with their specific banking needs the firms main goal is to provide the best possible financial products and services exceptional customer service and a unique a personal touch secretary director  chief credit officer current renasant bank part of renasant corp renasant bank is a company headquartered in tupelo ms focused on state commercial banks edward robinson mcgraw is the ceo in this role since  membercommunity bankers counsel current south carolina bankers association provide services to member banks boards  committees corporate boards ▾ secretary director  chief credit officer current renasant bank part of renasant corp renasant bank is a company headquartered in tupelo ms focused on state commercial banks edward robinson mcgraw is the ceo in this role since  public holdings restricted data only for relsci professional users start my free trial ➤ see more other affiliations m j huggins iii is affiliated with carolina financial corp crescom bank renasant bank south carolina bankers association renasant bank youve reached your  free profiles limit this month upgrade to relsci pro today to enjoy unlimited article views and much more start my free trial ➤ still not convinced check out our full listing of features here are you a relsci pro subscriber login to relsci pro  ➤ not a pro subscriber log in here to manage your alerts keep me signed in login  ➤ forgot your password i have read the lexisnexis terms  conditions sign me up  ➤ stock screener  yahoo financehomemailflickrtumblrnewssportsfinancecelebrityanswersgroupsmobilemoreyahoosearchsearchus markets closedsp 7 dow  listenwho is the face 